8:
Looks like you're all set. See you've got
a sword, huh? A bold choice, for a
brave guy.
15:
Nah, it's nothing. Anyways, let's get a
move on. We're not gonna find any
treasure while chatting up here!
31: How you doing on your end, Alk?
36: Fine! I managed to take it down!
39:
Not bad, kid. I thought I'd be babysitting,
but you're actually a pretty good fighter.
46:
Still too early to get ahead of yourself,
though.
58: What? First time seeing one in action?
61: No, it just got me thinking, is all.
65: Well, it was about time we took a break.
73:
You've got something on your mind,
right? Spill, or it'll bug me what's
bugging you.
79:
I kinda thought spears might be a good
option.
85:
I guess it'd be cool to learn how to use
a spear. I wish I could do lunges like you.
87:
I never put any thought into my choice
of weapon. I've always used a sword
because, well, that's what I've always
used.
90:
Nah, I'm gonna stop you there.
If you're a swordsman, stick to swords.
92: I think what you've got suits you.
98:
Yeah. See, spears have a long reach,
but they're not good for fighting
up-close. You've gotta take opponents
down from a distance.
100:
Spears are for people—cowards—who
pick off enemies before they get a
chance to fight back.
106:
But YOU'RE not a coward. A coward
wouldn't have saved me from that
pickpocket yesterday.
109:
A coward wouldn't agree to train in the
Kaleidoscope with only a kid for backup.
111:
You wouldn't be here teaching me
out of the goodness of your heart if—
115: Enough! Enough, already! I get it...
117:
You know what, you're not the right kind
of guy to take on the Kaleidoscope solo.
125:
You aren't the kind of guy who'd need to.
You're a real team player.
128:
Introduce to me your party some time.
If they can deal with a guy like me,
I'd like to try running the dungeons
with 'em.
131:
I'm sure they'd love to have you!
I know I would!
134: Heh, guess we've got a deal then.
138:
I tend to keep people at a distance, but
this kid... Man, he slipped right past my
defenses.
140: Now THAT'S a skill to be reckoned with.
